# UI Background Rules

## Context

- Apply when styling page backgrounds, screen containers, or main app shells.
- Backgrounds must never be flat or solid colors.
- Always use the 3-layer background recipe: base gradient + halftone dots + radial burst rays.

## Requirements

### Background Structure

- Implement background as 3 layers using CSS pseudo-elements.
- Base layer: purple gradient (`linear-gradient(180deg, #413DE1 0%, #8164ED 100%)`).
- Middle layer: halftone dots overlay (subtle, soft-light blend).
- Top layer: radial burst rays centered behind main card (optional but on-brand).

### Base Gradient Layer

- Use class `.bg-arcade` for the base gradient.
- Gradient: `linear-gradient(180deg, #413DE1 0%, #8164ED 100%)`.
- Position: `relative` with `overflow: hidden`.

### Halftone Dots Overlay

- Implement using `::before` pseudo-element.
- Pattern: `radial-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,0.18) 1.2px, transparent 1.2px)`.
- Background size: `10px 10px`.
- Opacity: `0.55`.
- Mix-blend-mode: `soft-light`.
- Pointer-events: `none`.

### Radial Burst Rays Overlay

- Implement using `::after` pseudo-element.
- Pattern: `repeating-conic-gradient(from 0deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.14) 0deg 8deg, rgba(255,255,255,0) 8deg 16deg)`.
- Position: `inset: -40%` to extend beyond viewport.
- Mask: `radial-gradient(circle at 50% 40%, rgba(0,0,0,1) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0) 60%)`.
- Opacity: `0.45`.
- Pointer-events: `none`.

### Non-Negotiable Rule

- Never ship a flat solid background.
- Always include at least the base gradient + halftone dots.
- Radial burst rays are optional but recommended for main screens.

## Examples

<example>
  Valid background implementation:
  
  ```css
  .bg-arcade {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #413DE1 0%, #8164ED 100%);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  
  .bg-arcade::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image: radial-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,0.18) 1.2px, transparent 1.2px);
    background-size: 10px 10px;
    opacity: 0.55;
    mix-blend-mode: soft-light;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  
  .bg-arcade::after {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: -40%;
    background: repeating-conic-gradient(
      from 0deg,
      rgba(255,255,255,0.14) 0deg 8deg,
      rgba(255,255,255,0) 8deg 16deg
    );
    mask-image: radial-gradient(circle at 50% 40%, rgba(0,0,0,1) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0) 60%);
    opacity: 0.45;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  ```
</example>

